                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d957">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3027.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Consul at Chihuahua</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 3, 3 p.m. Make the widest and most emphatic public denial of any
                    intention whatsoever on the part of this Government to <pb facs="0852" n="736"
                        xml:id="pg_736"/> intervene in Mexico. Make this statement as under express
                    instructions to do so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
